[ANALYSIS]
The experiment `bow_advanced_20260514_190416_run_01` successfully achieved an F1 score of 0.7246 and accuracy of 0.7625 using a BoW (Bag of Words) advanced architecture with specific hyperparameters tailored for character and word n-grams. The model's performance suggests that the combination of character-level features up to 5-grams and word-level features up to 2-grams, along with a logistic regression penalty parameter (`logreg_c`) set to 4.0, was effective in capturing the complexity of the text data. However, the experiment could have been improved by exploring different threshold values or adjusting the `min_df` parameter to potentially reduce noise and improve model robustness. For the next run, consider experimenting with a wider range of `logreg_c` values and varying the `word_ngram_max` to see if higher-order word n-grams can further enhance performance. Additionally, incorporating more sophisticated feature extraction techniques or ensemble methods might yield better results.